text:
Got the take away cup (with ice). It was spoilt.

I made the mistake of going after 3 pm. Apparently they do ice only take away after 3. That’s fine, but I guess they pack the remaining product at the end of the day. That’s probably the reason it was spoilt. Long day + time to pack drink. It smelt and tasted funky (I eat chendol once a week or so … I know exactly what it should smell/taste like).

There was no customers and yet the bowls were sold out, a huge price difference between the bowl ($2SGD) and the takeaway cup ($3SGD).
No red beans are included, so avoid if you prefer authentic Chendol.
Utter waste of time and money.
Not recommended.
It’s like cendol drink more than cendol dessert. Taste is refreshing but I miss the red beans!

The cendol is really a refreshing treat
though it’s less chewy, I still love it.

Well known stall at Geylang Serai food centre.
Selling traditional malay cendol. Nice!
